  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0bae\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bb2\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0bb0\u0ba3\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0bb0\u0bae\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb5\u0bc8 \u0b9c\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0baa\u0ba4\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b87\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0ba8\u0bc0\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb5\u0bc7\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd - \u0bb5\u0bbe\u0b9a\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bc7\u0bb5 \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0ba3\u0baf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb0",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "People should remove Ranil Wickramasinghe from the post of President with strength - Vasudeva Nanayakkara",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "If the President-led All-Party Government is formed, we will decide whether to join it or not based on its economic policy. We are of the position that Ranil Wickramasinghe should be removed from that post with the strength of the people, said Vasudeva Nanayakkara, leader of the Democratic Left Front and Member of Parliament.",
        "He mentioned this while attending a press conference held by the Socialist People's Front in Colombo yesterday.",
        "We brought Gotabaya Rajapakse to the presidency to bring a new socialist economic policy against neo-liberalism. But through the 20th Amendment, Basil Rajapakse, an American citizen, was brought into Parliament and given the Finance Ministry.",
        "It seemed to us that it was not possible to advance our economic policy through this. We in the Cabinet kept rejecting Basil Rajapakse's proposals to take decisions along liberal lines.",
        "Later, when the coalition of 10 parties took steps to remove Basil Rajapaksh from the cabinet, Basil Rajapaksh took steps to remove us from the cabinet on March 2nd. However, the people's struggle came to a head due to the benefit of our campaign among the people and due to the economic hardship caused to the people. Because of this, Basil Rajapaksh resigned. Subsequently, Mahinda Rajapaksh, who was the Prime Minister, resigned.",
        "Also, he appointed Ranil Wickramasinghe as Prime Minister in violation of our agreement of an all-party government that we made with Gotabaya Rajapaksa to solve the problems. However, the President resigned due to the continued protest of the protesters demanding that both the President and the Prime Minister resign.",
        "But Ranil Wickramasinghe, who was the Prime Minister, is holding the post of President against the people's mandate. Therefore, we are of the position that Ranil Wickramasinghe should be removed by people by force.",
        "Also, we have been saying from the beginning that an all-party government should be formed for the economic crisis the country is facing and the National Assembly should be formed on how to solve it.",
        "Currently, steps are being taken to form an all-party government under the leadership of President Ranil Wickramasinghe. Whoever forms an all-party government, if the economic policy of that government is neoliberalism, we will not join that government. So we will support the socialist economic policy.",
        "Also, President Ranil Wickramasinghe is currently working to strengthen the United National Party rather than building the country. For that he has taken steps to pull the opposition MPs to his side. He is trying to take MPs from United People's Shakti. He said that 2 people have already joined him."
      ],
